                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="contoh-percakapan-asking-opinion-dan-giving-opinion-minimal-10%e2%80%8b">
                            17. contoh percakapan asking opinion dan giving opinion minimal 10​</h2><br />
                        <p><strong>Jawaban:</strong></p><p>Kinan: Kania, please help me choosing the best dress to wear tonight.</p><p>Kania: Okay. What occasion is it?</p><p>Kinan: It’s my best friend’s birthday party.</p><p>Kania: Oh, I see.</p><p>Kinan: What do you think about this one?</p><p>Kania: Uhmm.. I think it’s too bright. Do you have another color?</p><p>Kinan: What about this one?</p><p>Kania: Oh, that’s nice. I would say it suits your height and skin color.</p><p>Kinan: Thank you, Kania.</p><p></p><p>2.)Haikal: Hi, guys! Have you heard about the new rules in our school?</p><p>Dirga: Yeah.</p><p>Haikal: What do you think?</p><p>Dirga: Personally I think that arriving at school before 6.30 is too early. We don’t have time to have breakfast.</p><p>Jerry: I don’t think it’s bad. We can wake up and go to school earlier.</p><p>Haikal: Yeah, I see your point, Jerry. But, it will extend our school hours. In my point of view, studying in such a long hours is ineffective.</p><p>Dirga: Yeah, I heard that some student council members would talk to the teachers so that they could reconsider that point.</p><p>Jerry: Uhmm.. I see. For me, it doesn’t matter if we should arrive at school before 6.30, but if you guys have any objection to the rules, maybe it is better if the rules are changed as before</p><p></p><p>3.)Vio: Good afternoon, friends. I would talk to the point. Today I got three options about the closing event. The first one is a mini concert, the second one is a color run, and the last is a costume party. What do you guys think about these options?</p><p>Lana: I think the second option is fun. Many people will join that kind of event.</p><p>Sheila: Well, I don’t think everyone like that kind of activity. Maybe a mini concert is the best option. We can invite one or two guests to attract the audience.</p><p>Dirga: Yeah, some people is not really into sport activity. Okay, what about you, Fikri?</p><p>Fikri: In my opinion, costume party is the best choice. Why? Because we don’t have to raise large funds. It’s a simple one, I guess.</p><p>Dirga: Oh, that’s right. Lana and Sheila, what do you think about this? Do you agree with Fikri’s opinion?</p><p>Lana: Yeah, I think it’s also fun.</p><p>Sheila: That’s a reasonable opinion. So, yeah, I agree with you, Fikri.</p><p>Dirga: Okay. Now we’ve decided the closing event. Tomorrow we’ll talk about the details</p><p><strong>Penjelasan:</strong></p><p>semoga mmbntu:)</p><br />
                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="buat-10-kalimat-materi-tentang-opinion-and-thought%e2%80%8b">
                            18. buat 10 kalimat materi tentang opinion and thought​</h2><br />
                        <p><strong>Opinion and thought​:</strong></p><p>-Most of people do not agree with my opinion (banyak orang tidak setuju dengan pendapatku).</p><p>- Almost everyone think she is smart (hampir setiap orang berpikir bahwa dia pandai).</p><p>-In my opinion this agenda must be implemented immediately (menurut pendapatku acara ini harus segera dilaksanakan).</p><p>-I think this event is held on campus (saya pikir acara ini dilakukan di kampus)..</p><p>-I agree with your opinion (saya setuju dengan pendapatmu)</p><p>- Of course (tentu saja).</p><p>-That is a good point  (itu poin yang bagus).</p><p>- I don’t believe that (saya tidak setuju dengan itu)</p><p>- I disagree with you (saya tidak setuju dengan pendapatmu)</p><p>-  I think you are wrong (saya pikir kamu salah).</p><p></p><p></p><p><strong>Pembahasan:</strong></p><p><strong>Opinions </strong>are a means to express thoughts or feelings about something. This opinion can be about a person or thing. Well, when we want to express an opinion, it is important to provide reasons or examples to strengthen our opinion.</p><p>When you want to give an opinion, or thoughts, then you have to understand first, you are giving a personal opinion (personal opinion) or general opinion (general opinion). Here's an expression you can use.</p><p><strong>1. Expressions of General Opinions</strong></p><p>This expression is used to give an opinion in general, or according to a general view. this general view is a counterbalance and helps to avoid absolute opinion.</p><p>example:</p><p>a. Most of people do not agree with my opinion (banyak orang tidak setuju dengan pendapatku)</p><p>b. Almost everyone think she is smart (hampir setiap orang berpikir bahwa dia pandai)</p><p><strong>2. Expressions of Personal Opinions</strong></p><p>This expression is used to convey views, opinions or thoughts personally.</p><p>a. In my opinion this agenda must be implemented immediately (menurut pendapatku acara ini harus segera dilaksanakan)</p><p>b. I think this event is held on campus (saya pikir acara ini dilakukan di kampus).</p><p><strong>3. Agreeing with an opinion</strong></p><p>If you agree with an opinion, then you can express it as follows:</p><p>example:</p><p>a. I agree with your opinion (saya setuju dengan pendapatmu)</p><p>b. Of course (tentu saja)</p><p>c. That is a good point  (itu poin yang bagus). etc</p><p><strong>4. Disagreeing with an opinion</strong></p><p>Well, if you don't agree with the opinion of your friends or other people, then you can use the following expression.</p><p>a. I don’t believe that (saya tidak setuju dengan itu)</p><p>b. I disagree with you (saya tidak setuju dengan pendapatmu)</p><p>c. I think you are wrong (saya pikir kamu salah)</p><p></p><p><strong>Pelajari Lebih Lanjut </strong></p><p>1. Contoh percakapan asking opinion https://brainly.co.id/tugas/3190741</p><p>2. Contoh percakapan opinion https://brainly.co.id/tugas/381731</p><p>3. Perbedaan asking opinion dan giving opinion https://brainly.co.id/tugas/3059748</p><p></p><p><strong>Detail Jawaban</strong></p><p>Kelas: 8</p><p>Mapel: Bahasa Inggris</p><p>Bab: 1</p><p>Kode: 8.5.1</p><p></p><p><strong>#AyoBelajar</strong></p><p><strong>#SPJ2</strong></p><p></p><br />
                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="contoh-kalimat-asking-opinion-giving-opinion-dan-responding-opinion-masing-masing-5-plis-jawab">
                            19. Contoh kalimat asking opinion, giving opinion dan responding opinion masing masing 5 plis jawab</h2><br />
                        <p><strong>Jawaban:</strong></p><p>asking opinion= What do you think about my cut new hair? </p><p>giving opinion = l think is it too Short</p><p><strong>Penjelasan:</strong></p><p>maaf kalo salah</p><p></p><br />
                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="buatlah-10-kalimat-asking-opinion-menanyakan-pendapat-dalam-situasi-formal-dan-informal">
                            20. Buatlah 10 kalimat asking opinion (menanyakan pendapat) dalam situasi formal dan informal</h2><br />
                        What do you think? (Bagaimana menurutmu?)<p></p><p></p>Do you see what I'm getting at? (Apakah Anda mengerti apa yang saya maksud?)<p></p><p></p>Do you know/see what I mean? (Apakah Anda tahu / mengerti apa yang saya maksud?)<p></p><p></p><br />
                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="10-contoh-kalimat-opinion-dalam-bentuk-bahasa-inggris">
                            21. 10 contoh kalimat opinion dalam bentuk bahasa inggris</h2><br />
                        <p>Kalimat opinion dalam bahasa inggris merupakan jenis kalimat yang digunaka untuk mengungkapkan pendapat. Kalimat opinion dapat dinyatakan dengan penggunaan expression of giving opinion (ungkapan pemberian pendapat). Berikut penjelasannya.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Penjelasan:</strong></p><p>Expression of giving opinion merupakan ungkapan yang digunakan untuk menyampaikan pendapat, ide, gagasan, maupun pandangan terhadap sesuatu. Berikut beberapa expression of giving opinion yang umum digunakan:
</p><p>1. I think (that) ...
</p><p>2. I feel (that) ...
</p><p>3. In my opinion, ...
</p><p>4. For me, ...
</p><p>5. It is my opinion that ...
</p><p>
</p><p><strong>Berikut contoh kalimat yang menggunakan expression of giving opinion.</strong>
</p><p>1.	I think we should bring an umbrella.
</p><p>2.	In my opinion, this restaurant is expensive.
</p><p>3.	I feel Captain America is better than Ironman.
</p><p>4.	I think I have to tell you the truth.
</p><p>5.	It is my opinion that we have to rearrange the structure of the organization.
</p><p>6.	For me, it is better to discuss it later.
</p><p>7.	I think this cake is delicious.
</p><p>8.	I feel that global economic collapse is caused by corona virus.
</p><p>9.	It is my opinion that we should provide health insurance for the staffs.
</p><p>10.	For me, money is not everything but everything needs money.
</p><p>
</p><p>Semoga membantu.
</p><p>
